# Customer data + session outputs — NEVER committed.
# Intake's priors generation writes RoleContext outputs here; per-session state lives
# in sessions/. These are local-only by policy — they contain real customer
# transcripts, RoleContext priors derived from them, and inception-pipeline session
# state. None of this belongs in the public repo. Local-only is also where our own
# research / validation work on specific customer use cases lives.
skills/
sessions/
intake/sources/
agent/inception/sample_feedback/

# Inception's agent_starter/ outputs — generated artifacts per use case, local-only
agent_starter/

# Reference docs / case studies we author internally but don't ship publicly
# (our customer-specific validation work lives here on disk, not in git)
docs/internal/
research/

# Patterns curator audit-trail artifacts — useful locally for inspecting
# `promote` runs, but accumulate noise over time. The `.candidate.md` files
# (one per promoted cluster) ARE tracked so humans can review + commit
# approved promotions; `.promotion_runs/*.json` are run-level audit JSON
# that adds little to history.
patterns/.promotion_runs/
